# styles/.builderrules — Token & Theming Rules

## Token usage

- Always prefer CSS custom properties (tokens) over hardcoded values for color, spacing,
  typography, border-radius, shadow, and z-index.
- Token file: `styles/tokens.css` — `@theme` block auto-generates Tailwind utilities.
- If a token is missing, add it to the `@theme` block rather than using a raw value.

## Color token tiers

The color scales have three tiers; use the right one:

| Tier | Suffixes | Use |
|------|----------|-----|
| Backgrounds | 50, 100 | Section fills, card tints, status backgrounds |
| Interactive / text | 600, 700 | Buttons, links, body text on white — all pass WCAG AA |
| Deep / dark | 800, 900, 950 | Dark hero backgrounds, high-contrast accents |

Do NOT use 200–500 tier tokens for text on white backgrounds — they fail WCAG AA contrast.

## Gradient utilities

Use the pre-built gradient classes instead of writing gradient CSS from scratch:

| Class | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `gradient-brand` | CTAs, active states, primary backgrounds |
| `gradient-brand-subtle` | Section fills, card tints |
| `gradient-brand-dark` | Dark hero sections, banners |
| `gradient-mesh` | Hero backgrounds, marketing splash sections |
| `gradient-brand-text` | Heading text — never use on body copy |

## Design System Indexing rules

When indexing design tokens for Builder DSI:

- Include the 600 and 700 level color tokens as the primary interactive palette.
- Include the 50 and 100 level tokens as the background/surface palette.
- Include all five gradient utility classes as named utilities.
- Exclude primitive mid-range tokens (200–500 suffix) from the indexed palette —
  they exist for fine-tuning, not as primary choices.
- Group tokens by semantic role: `brand`, `accent`, `success`, `warning`, `error`.
